result.execSummary:
Joseph Daniel Gaudreau was extradited to another county, state or jurisdiction. Extradition means Joseph Daniel Gaudreau was accused or convicted of an offense in another county, state or jurisdiction and was taken there to face their charge(s) or conviction.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Called at 10:28 AM. Joseph Gaudreau (1/19/88). Gaudreau appears in person and in custody without counsel. State appear by Charles Simono. Here for extradition hearing. Gaudreau aware that State of Michigan has a current warrant for him. Court goes thru extradition collaquey and governor's warrant and right to attorney. Gaudreau reviews warrant paperwork and will waive extradition voluntarily and signs appropriate paperwork. Court finds the defendant has freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived extradition and signs the order. Adjourned at 10:34 AM.
